        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 5:39PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 538 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Hay Springs, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rushville, Hay Springs, Highway 250 crossing the Niobrara River,
Intersection of Highway 87 and Antelope Road, and Walgren Lake State
Recreation Area.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 20 between mile markers 79 and 97.
Highway 250 between mile markers 32 and 48.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
